    "recap_headline": "College of Charleston",
    "recap_text": "MT PLEASANT, S.C. \u2013\nGraduate\nDylan Johnson\nwent 2-for-3 with 3 RBI as College of Charleston baseball beat UNCW 6-3 Sunday afternoon at Patriots Point.\nThe Cougars improve to 10-13 overall and 5-4 in the CAA while handing the Seahawks their first conference loss of the season (16-8, 5-1 CAA).\nJohnson and freshman\nJake Amman\nhomered for Charleston while redshirt junior\nCarson Bryant\nand freshman\nKaden Myers\ncombined to allow just one run across the first 6.1 innings.\nCRITICAL POINTS AGAINST UNCW:\nCharleston jumped on UNCW early when Johnson doubled in a pair in the bottom of the first.\nRedshirt sophomore\nJackson Berini\ndoubled the Cougar lead in the third with a two-run double of his own.\nBryant made his sixth start of the campaign, allowing just one hit in three scoreless innings.\nAmman made is a 5-0 contest when he led off the fourth with a solo shot to center.\nJohnson collected his second extra base hit of the afternoon with a solo homer of his own in the sixth.\nMyers continued to keep the UNCW bats quiet as he earned his third win of the year following 3.1 frames.\nGraduate\nKurt Rogers\nstruck out three in 1.1 innings as he picked up his second save.\nOF NOTE:\nCharleston is 26-29 against UNCW in the all-time series and improves to 17-13 at home.\nJohnson had his eighth multi-hit game of the year and third multi-RBI performance.\nAmman has multiple hits in seven contests.\nMyers earned his second conference victory and lowered his ERA in league play to 2.13.\nCofC has had two home runs in a game four times this year.\nUP NEXT:\nCharleston concludes its homestand March 25 with a midweek matchup against Georgia Southern. First pitch from Patriots Point is slated for 6 p.m.\nFor complete coverage of Charleston baseball, follow us X (@CofCBaseball) and Instagram (@CofC_Baseball).",
